  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you know if you cat loves you?",
  "response": "Cats can show affection in a variety of ways. Here are some common signs that your cat loves you:\n\n1. **Purring:** Cats often purr when they are content, and if your cat purrs while being around you, it's a good sign they're happy and feel safe.\n\n2. **Head Butting and Rubbing:** Cats have scent glands on their heads. When they bump their heads or rub against you, they're marking you with their scent, which indicates trust and affection.\n\n3. **Slow Blinks:** If your cat looks at you and slowly blinks, it's like a kitty kiss. Slow blinking is a sign of trust and love in the feline world.\n\n4. **Bringing You \"Gifts\":** Cats are natural hunters, and if they bring you toys or even the occasional real prey, they're sharing their successes and showing care.\n\n5. **Following You Around:** Cats that follow you around or hang out in the same room with you are showing that they enjoy your company.\n\n6. **Sleeping on or Near You:** Cats feel vulnerable when they sleep, so choosing to sleep on or near you shows that they trust you completely.\n\n7. **Kneading:** This behavior, where a cat rhythmically pushes their paws into you, is a leftover from kittenhood when they would knead their mother for milk. Kneading on you indicates they feel comfortable and content.\n\n8. **Tail Position:** A cat's tail can tell a lot about their mood. If their tail is upright and curls at the top like a question mark, it usually means they are happy to see you.\n\n9. **Licking:** Cats groom themselves regularly, and if they lick you, they're treating you as part of their family, which is a strong sign of affection.\n\n10. **Exposing Their Belly:** When cats lie on their back and expose their belly, they're showing trust. Only do this if you're confident your cat enjoys belly rubs, as some cats might prefer not to be touched there.\n\nKeep in mind that every cat expresses affection differently, so understanding your individual cat\u2019s behavior is key.",
